\f0\fs24 \cf0 # myaircraft.us \'97 Product + Technical Build Spec\
\
## Project Summary\
Build **myaircraft.us**, a multi-tenant aviation document intelligence platform for aircraft owners, mechanics, flight schools, and operators.\
\
Users can upload:\
- aircraft logbooks\
- POH / AFM / AFM supplements\
- maintenance manuals\
- service manuals\
- parts catalogs / IPC\
- work orders\
- inspection reports\
- 337s / 8130s\
- service bulletins\
- airworthiness directives\
- related aircraft documents\
\
The platform must ingest documents from:\
1. direct PDF upload\
2. Google Drive import\
\
After upload, the system should:\
- parse documents\
- split them into pages and semantic chunks\
- generate embeddings using OpenAI\
- store embeddings and metadata in Supabase\
- organize all records by tenant and aircraft\
- provide a chat interface that answers questions only from uploaded records\
- return exact citations with document name, page number, section, chunk, and snippet\
- reduce hallucinations by refusing to answer when evidence is insufficient\
\
---\
\
## Core Product Requirements\
\
### Multi-tenant architecture\
Each organization must have complete data isolation.\
\
Entities:\
- Organization / Tenant\
- Users\
- Aircraft\
- Documents\
- Document Versions\
- Queries\
- Citations\
\
### Aircraft-based organization\
Every document should be attachable to a specific aircraft.\
\
Aircraft metadata:\
- tail number\
- serial number\
- make\
- model\
- year\
- engine model\
- propeller model\
- operator\
- base location (optional)\
\
### Document categories\
Support at minimum:\
- Logbooks\
- POH\
- AFM\
- AFM Supplements\
- Maintenance Manual\
- Service Manual\
- Parts Catalog / IPC\
- AD / SB / SL\
- Work Orders\
- Inspection Reports\
- 337 / 8130 / certification documents\
- Miscellaneous\
\
### Upload methods\
#### Direct upload\
- drag and drop PDF upload\
- multiple file upload\
- folder upload if practical\
\
#### Google Drive\
- connect user Google account\
- select files/folders\
- ingest selected PDFs and supported files\
- store source metadata and source URL\
\
