\
## Non-Negotiable Product Principles\
\
1. Never answer from general model memory if tenant documents do not support the answer.\
2. Every factual answer must include citations.\
3. If evidence is insufficient, say so clearly.\
4. Page-level traceability is mandatory.\
5. The original file is always the source of truth.\
6. Maintain audit logs for uploads, processing, and queries.\
\
---\
\
## Parsing and Ingestion Pipeline\
\
### Step 1: upload intake\
On upload:\
- create document record\
- attach tenant_id and aircraft_id\
- store original file in Supabase Storage\
- calculate checksum\
- assign document type\
- mark status = queued\
\
### Step 2: parse document\
For each PDF:\
- detect if text-native PDF\
- if text-native: extract page text directly\
- if scanned: run OCR\
- preserve page boundaries\
- preserve document title and section headings when possible\
- create page records\
\
### Step 3: chunking\
Chunking rules:\
- chunk by semantic section when possible\
- preserve page number in every chunk\
- target chunk size around 500-1000 tokens\
- overlap chunks by ~10-15%\
- store section title and neighboring context\
\
### Step 4: embeddings\
For each chunk:\
- prepend metadata header before embedding, including:\
  - aircraft make/model\
  - document type\
  - document title\
  - section title\
  - page number\
- generate embedding with OpenAI\
- store vector in Supabase pgvector\
\
### Step 5: extracted metadata\
Attempt structured extraction for:\
- tail number\
- serial number\
- document revision\
- manual title\
- effective date\
- references to components\
- inspection types\
- total time / tach time if visible\
- dates mentioned in entries\
\
Store extracted metadata separately from raw text.\
